# Tmux

## Prefix

The <prefix> is a key combination that needs to be used to trigger commands.

<prefix> = <space> b

## Hotkeys

| Combination | Description               | Notes                           |
| ----------- | ------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| <prefix> "  | Split window vertically   | Horizontal separator            |
| <prefix> %  | Split window horizontally | Vertical separator              |
| <prefix> j  | Focus pane below          |                                 |
| <prefix> k  | Focus pane above          |                                 |
| <prefix> l  | Focus pane on the right   |                                 |
| <prefix> h  | Focus pane on the left    |                                 |
| <prefix> J  | Resize pane down          | Move the separator down         |
| <prefix> K  | Resize pane up            | Move the separator up           |
| <prefix> L  | Resize pane to the right  | Move the separator to the right |
| <prefix> H  | Resize pane to the left   | Move the separator to the left  |
| <prefix> R  | Reload tmux configuration |                                 |
| <prefix> x  | Close pane                |                                 |
| <prefix> I  | Install tmux plugins      |                                 |
| <prefix> U  | Update tmux plugins       |                                 |

